article.headline: Central Connecticut 79, St. Francis, N.Y. 61
article.story: NEW BRITAIN, Conn. (AP) -- Tristan Blackwood had 25 points and Obie Nwadike added 23 to lead Central Connecticut to a 79-61 victory over St. Francis of New York in the quarterfinals of the Northeast Conference Tournament Thursday night. Nwadike also grabbed 11 rebounds for the top-seeded Blue Devils (20-11). CCSU will play Mount St. Mary's in a semifinal on Sunday. Mount St. Mary's, the No. 5 seed, advanced with a 78-61 win over Robert Morris Thursday. Marcus Williams led St. Francis (9-22) with 16 points. The Blue Devils led by four at halftime then pulled away midway through the second period. A putback by Nwadike was followed by five CCSU free throws during a 7-0 spurt to make it 53-42 with just under 11 minutes to play. St. Francis was already over the foul limit 11 minutes into the second half, and the Blue Devils took advantage, hitting 15 of their first 18 free throws in the second half. The Terriers jumped out to a 14-4 lead just 3:45 into the game by hitting seven of their first eight shots. Central countered with a 16-0 run, using a strong inside game. Center Jemino Sobers had a dunk and a floater in the lane during the spurt, and Nwadike scored off a pair of cuts to the basket. Central led by as many as eight down the stretch and had a 32-28 lead at the break.
